.TH GIT-HUNKS 1 "2026-01-18" "git-hunks" "Git Manual"
.SH NAME
git-hunks \- non-interactive selective hunk staging
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git hunks
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Non-interactive selective hunk staging for git. Designed for use by
AI agents and scripts.
.PP
Hunk IDs use the format \fBfile:@\-old,len+new,len\fR based on the
diff's @@ header, so they remain stable even when other hunks are staged.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list [\-\-staged]
List all hunks with unique IDs. Use \fB\-\-staged\fR to list staged
hunks instead of unstaged.
.TP
.B add \fIhunk-id\fR [\fIhunk-id\fR ...]
Stage specific hunks by their ID.
.SH EXAMPLES
List all unstaged hunks:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ git hunks list
src/main.c:@-10,6+10,7
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@
 #include <stdio.h>
+#include <stdlib.h>
---
.fi
.RE
.PP
Stage a specific hunk:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ git hunks add 'src/main.c:@-10,6+10,7'
Staged: src/main.c:@-10,6+10,7
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-add (1),
.BR git-diff (1)
